    <td>
      <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center">
        <tr>
          <td bgcolor="#224372">
            <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="4">
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" background="images/forum-cell.gif" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">T O P I C&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R E V I E W</font></b></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><b>Kerhunge</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/08/2003&nbsp;: 12:31:51 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> This is a basic guide built on my experiences hunting in PoD. The exp is great, the mobs are easy, and there are slightly less idiots than Plane of Nightmare (which I refuse to ever hunt in).<br /><br />Map of Hunting Areas:<br /><img src="http://photopile.com/photos/gtamour/auctions/3888.jpg" border="0"><br /><br /><br />NOTE: The blue outline above Zone In is Grimmror Plaguebringer's pathing, a level 60 quest mob. I like to kill him by aggro kiting every now and then just for ****s and giggles. he gives 8% AA though hehe<br /><br /><br /><br />Recommended Other Class Buffs:<br /><br />SoW/Sow Potions (important)<br />Optional: Virtue/Aego/PoTC-9 series<br /><br />I will address each area on the map, which levels are best for the area, and spell lineup/pull information below.<br /><br />#1. Tsetsian Flies<br />Recommended Level: 51-54<br />EXP: Above Average<br />Difficulty: Low to Moderate<br />Competition: High to Very High<br />Danger: Medium<br />Respawn: 20 minutes<br /><br />When nearing area #1 on the map, you should see a rock surrounded by a fairly clear area to the right, with flies over the hill just a little ways. This area in front of the rock will be your pull area.<br /><br />Recommended Spell lineup<br /><br />Lifetap<br />Bond of Death<br />level 4 fear (will explain)<br />Dooming Darkness<br />Splurt<br />Ignite blood (Swap for pet buff)<br />Lich<br />Feign<br /><br />NOTE: Always keep DMF and SoW up. Turn pet taunt OFF<br /><br />Once your pet is guarded, hasted, and you have enough mana that makes you comfortable, run Northeast, looking slightly over the hill. There should be 4 flies, along with the occasional roamer Swamp Rat or Larvae. Once there are no roamers visible, pull the closest fly on the left with darkness. If you get two, let them come at you a little ways (about halfway to you) then feign. Wait until the unsnared paths back to spawn, stand, and resnare the original fly.<br /><br />Kite fly #1 back to pet, casting Ignite/Splurt before pet attacks. Cast level 4 fear, then send pet. The key method is not letting your pet get aggro. The fly will run off, but won't move far away before fear breaks. Continue to reapply fear each time to comes close to you (not close enough to hit you though). Resnare if needed at about 75 seconds into the fight. They have low resists, but there is always that blurb that could be trouble!<br /><br />Continue kiting, reapplying dots if necessary until dead. Rinse and repeat with the remaining flies (you will probably have to feign break 1-2 more times). If you find yourself hot to trot on the mana and no flies are up, pull a diseased rat from the area behind you. I would actually suggest aggro kiting these (letting dots take it down to around 90% before sending pet).<br /><br /><br />#2 Rats<br /><br />Recommended Level: 53<br />EXP: Above Average<br />Difficulty: Medium<br />Competition: Medium to High<br />Danger: High<br /><br />Personally I wouldn't touch this camp with a twenty foot pole, as it's full of druids/bards, and adds adds adds. Avoid this camp unless you want a hassle.<br /><br />#3 Bone Wall Goo's and Rats<br /><br />Recommended Level: 53-57<br />EXP: Above Average<br />Difficulty: Low to Moderate<br />Competition: Low to Medium<br />Danger: Medium<br /><br />This is a prime leveling spot for necro's, even after the pathing change. Move to spot #3 on the map and look ahead, there should be a hill with a few hairs on it blocking your view. This is your fearkiting plain.<br /><br />Recommended Spells<br /><br />Lifetap<br />Bond<br />Invoke Fear<br />Dooming Darkness<br />Rogue/Monk pet (taunt off)<br />Ignite<br />Splurt until 56, then Cessation of Corr<br />Lich<br />Feign<br /><br />If you look on the map, pulling to the rock on the  right hand side of bone wall, and fearing from there, the mobs will take the path of the blue line with invoke fear.<br /><br />Pulling: Run over the hill and look for the nearest mob by itself. I would avoid pestilent rats until 55-57, and run away FAST if you see an Arachnae Crawler coming near you. These will ruin your day.<br /><br />Pull the mob with Dooming, stacking on Cessation right away, then Ignite or Bond depending on how your HP is. Speed off down the hill towards your pet, sit down, wait. Once he gets within casting range, resnare, then wait until he gets half that distance again. Send pet, then cast Invoke Fear. Fear should hit right as pet engages. <br /><br />Cessation will wear off soon after, so stack it again along with ignite if you hadn't already. Refresh fear as needed, making sure to keep enough aggro that it runs back at you when fear breaks.  (Yo-Yo kiting in a way hehe)<br /><br />Rinse Lather Repeat. All mobs except some pestilent rats and about 75% of arachnae crawlers are fearable. Pile of Bile are the lowest, while feeble rats seem to have the highest resists of the fearable mobs.<br /><br />NOTE on #10. If you pull from this area to bone wall, the larvae are not fearable, and they will pop on you before they can get to that side of the river. I would suggest not bothering with this area.<br /><br />#4. Central Courtyard<br /><br />Recommended Level: 56-61<br />EXP: High<br />Difficulty: Above Average<br />Competition: Medium to High<br />Danger: High<br /><br />This is my second favorite camp of the CY's, mostly because I can pull them out and aggro kite in a more wide open area.<br /><br />Recommended Spells:<br /><br />SOW!<br />HP BUFFS!<br /><br />Deflux<br />BoD/Vexing<br />Level 4 Fear<br />Dooming Darkness<br />Ignite<br />Splurt<br />Lich<br />Feign<br /><br />Recommended pet: Monk<br /><br />NOTE: Affliction haste is VERY important here. If you cannot get a Ceramic Skull of Decay, purchase a AH2-3 item. The time off of dooming is necessary!<br /><br />Guard your pet in area #5 on the map, then run in the valley between bone wall. Look for a Lightcrawler Pest or a Diseased Lightcrawler, as they are the easiest to kill. Avoid pulling a Lightcrawler Defiler, as they harmtouch for the low 900's, and are resistant lil <img src="images/censored_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" />!<br /><br />when one is clear, pull with dooming and run out through bone wall. You should pass a bent hair, run past this for about 3 seconds and turn around, begin spamming your fear button. There is a pathing bug in this valley, that they will warp three times inside of it, and eventually will pop out under the bent hair. Cast fear, run towards pet, recast fear, run past pet, resnare, dot it, send pet. Continue recasting Dooming about every 60 seconds, as they are pretty resistant. Recast fear after first set of DoT's wear off, and continue kiting until dead. KEEP DMF ON. It will save you time to resnare. They Double hit and bash for around 357. Be warned!<br /><br />#6 NCY, RCY, etcetra<br /><br />Recommended Level: 56-62<br />EXP: HIGH<br />Difficulty: Above Average<br />Competition: High<br />Danger: High<br /><br />This is my favorite of the CY's. It has a large aggro kiting area at #6, and plentiful mobs. If snare breaks before you can resnare, run up the wall behind the bent hair (to your left of camp spot). This will buy you a coupla seconds. Use the same kiting techniques as #5. There are more Defilers here, as well as underbulks. I find underbulks are easier than lightcrawlers because they don't cover ground as quickly, but they will still own you if they catch you<img src="images/owned.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" />. Make sure to have decent magic resist 100+ preferred. If a defiler snares you, feign. They will catch up to you and love you like a lonely prison inmate<img src="images/shrug.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" />. <br /><br />NOTE: Be careful when getting too close to the castle wall. The mobs have a tendency to warp on you there. Try to kite between the hair to your right, and the back of the hair on your left in a circular motion!<br /><br />#7 SCY, LCY, etcetra<br /><br />Recommended Level: 56-62<br />EXP: High<br />Difficulty: Medium to High<br />Competition: Medium<br />Danger: Medium<br /><br />Same method as the previous NCY and #5 on the map. You will be kiting in a triangular pattern, with up on the wall against the castle being the start, then down to the first outcropping, then to the second hair, then back up to the zonewall+castle. This is tougher because the lack of room, however it's not camped as much. There are some warping issues if you hug the wall too close. Be warned. This isn't as dangerous though because there is some funky pathing here that will give you enough time to resnare without getting hit too much, but you have to find that yourself.<br /><br />#8 Guardians of the Crypt<br /><br />Recommended Level: 59-65<br />EXP: HIGH<br />Difficulty: Moderate to High<br />Competition: Less than for the kissing booth of a fat leper<img src="images/mybanana.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br />Danger: Moderate<br />Respawn: 20 minutes<br /><br />Before attempting this, load up Qvox, feign, and Harmshield. Sow is important too!. Once damage shield get up, run near the two magus at doorway in Central CY, punching harmshield first, and running up the stairs (straight, then to the left). Once you reach the top floor, HS should wear off. Punch QVOX immediately, and run south along the balcony and around the corner to feign (SCY area balcony). I find it is better to feign here because they take longer to get there, and therefore won't cast on you to break feign.<br /><br />Wait about 5 minutes for them to path back to spawn, stand up. Hug the edge of the balcony facing the rest of the desert and run towards #8. Don't worry, you can't fall off. SoE has childproofed it. Setup in the corner facing the stairway with the Guardians of the Crypt, and Gryme, the Big Fat Pain in the <img src="images/censored_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br /><br />Load up a pet, taunt off. EoT/LoZ preferred. Some people like to wait till 62 to root n rot these, but PFFFFT! That's ***! So we're gonna aggro kite. It's dangerous, but it sure beats sitting on your butt.<br /><br />Recommended Spells:<br /><br />Deflux/ToM<br />Vexing/Saryns<br />Invoke Fear (need the fast cast for aggro kiting. You won't run outta mana)<br />Dooming/Embracing darkness<br />Pyrocuror<br />Splurt<br />Arch Lich/SoS<br />Death peace recommended/Feign death<br /><br />Get full mana and run to guardians until close enough to cast. Make sure gryme is either at the top of the stairs, or inside the tunnel on the left before pulling. <br /><br />Cast dooming on the GoC to the right first. If it is resisted, feign and wait for them to reset. Continue until you get him snared, wait until the unsnared gets halfway to you, then feign. Wait until the roamer paths back and returns to spawn, stand, refresh snare, cast invoke fear twice (backing up each cast. Gotta get aggro). If you have time, splurt him, if not, run to your left in the middle of the balcony at all times, stopping before you get to the stairway you came up. Turn around, cast pyro, send pet, fear again. This is the hard part. You have to time it so that when he gets close, you run to the left, splitting the distance between you, then running to the last pillar facing you. Turn around, resnare as needed, reDoT as needed, fear occasionaly when you have time. If he paths too close to the wall near desert, he will pop on you and hit you for around 471 2 times, then a bash or kick. This is bad mmmkay, so try to keep him kited in a long rectangular shape.<br /><br />Pulling the top row: <img src="images/clueless.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><img src="images/speech/icon_speech_ugh.gif" border="0"><br /><br />Some folks find this hard, but it's all about timing. Run within casting range of the GoC on the right side, top floor. Wait until you see Gryme walk into the tunnel on the left, and count slowly to 12. Once you reach 12, snare him, run back. If you see the pink fatty. Feign. If not, use the same breaking method as the bottom two. <br /><br />Rinse and Repeat for kiting.<br /><br />The bottom mob should respawn soon after the fight is over, so not a lotta sit on your butt time at this camp.<br /><br />Using the 12 seconds, I have yet to get Gryme to aggro me on the top floor pull. You may want to adjust depending on how fast you count though<img src="images/jump2refection_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" />.<br /><br /><br />Anyways, that concludes my guide to Plane of Disease. If you have any questions, input, suggestions, or requests for other quides, please post them on this thread!<br /><br /><br />Kerhunge Mysticnight<br />Level 61 Unguilded Prexus Necro<br /><br />EDIT: Explained WTF blue outline was.<br /><br />EDIT: Correcting Spelling Errors</span></font></td>
